The paper focuses on learning from web data, specifically images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the issue of label noise and domain shift, which are common challenges in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of variational autoencoder (VAE), which is a popular technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
